claim.claim-text:
1. A pattern forming method, comprising: 
determining an allowable value of an etching conversion difference; 
obtaining a maximum distance between patterns generating said etching conversion difference within said allowable value, said patterns including main patterns or both main patterns and a dummy pattern; 
preparing a first design layout in which a first distance between said main patterns is smaller than said maximum distance, or a second design layout in which a second distance between said main patterns and said dummy pattern is smaller than said maximum distance; 
performing a design data conversion based on said first or second design layout to form first or second design data; and 
forming said main patterns by using said first design data, or forming both said main patterns and said dummy pattern by using said second design data.

15. A pattern forming method, comprising: 
determining an allowable value of an etching conversion difference; 
obtaining a maximum distance between patterns generating said etching conversion difference within said allowable value, said patterns including main patterns or both main patterns and a dummy pattern; 
determining a third distance between adjacent element regions; 
preparing in accordance with said third distance a design layout in which a fourth distance between said main patterns and edge portions of said element regions is not larger than a first defined value; 
performing conversion of a design data in view of said design layout and a first distance between said main patterns to prepare a first design data in the case where said third distance is not larger than a second defined value, or determining a width of said dummy pattern and performing conversion of a design data in view of said design layout, said width of said dummy pattern, and a second distance between said main patterns and said dummy pattern to prepare a second design data in the case where said third distance is not smaller than said second defined value, each of said first and second distances being not larger than said maximum distance; and 
forming said main patterns by using said first design data or forming both said main patterns and said dummy pattern by using said second design data.
